<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>DutchNews.nl</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/</link><description>DutchNews.nl brings daily news from The Netherlands in English</description><lastBuildDate>Fri, 31 May 2024 13:04:50 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Dutch volunteer dies fighting in Ukraine, ministry confirms</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/dutch-volunteer-dies-fighting-in-ukraine-ministry-confirms/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-236292 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-armed-forces"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Dutch volunteer dies fighting in Ukraine, ministry confirms</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-05-31T13:04:50+00:00"> May 31, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-57592" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_57592"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="268" sizes="(max-width: 378px) 100vw, 378px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/soldiers-marching-e1415395669786.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/soldiers-marching-e1415395669786.jpg 378w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/soldiers-marching-e1415395669786-300x212.jpg 300w" width="378"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-57592"> Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>A Dutch national who volunteered to fight for Ukraine has died on the battlefield, the foreign affairs ministry has confirmed.</p><p>The man is said to have joined the Ukrainian Foreign Legion and died on May 20 near Chasiv Yar in the north of the Donetsk region.</p><p>He is the third Dutch national known to have died fighting against Russia, but the foreign ministry does not have an overview of how many volunteers have gone, and how many have been killed.</p><p>Several dozen Dutch nationals went to the region shortly after the war began.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/armed-forces/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=236292</guid><pubDate>Fri, 31 May 2024 13:04:50 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Podcast: The Pulling a Dick Out of a Hat Edition</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/podcast-the-pulling-a-dick-out-of-a-hat-edition/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-236249 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-uncategorized type-podcast"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Podcast: The Pulling a Dick Out of a Hat Edition</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-05-31T10:18:43+00:00"> May 31, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-236253" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_236253"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1335" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Depositphotos_84036300_L.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Depositphotos_84036300_L.jpg 2000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Depositphotos_84036300_L-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Depositphotos_84036300_L-1200x801.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Depositphotos_84036300_L-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Depositphotos_84036300_L-768x513.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Depositphotos_84036300_L-1536x1025.jpg 1536w" width="2000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-236253"> Photo: Depositphotos</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p><a href="https://www.patreon.com/DutchNewsNL"><strong>Want to support the DutchNews podcast and keep up our stocks of stroopwafels and orange tompouces? Click here to become a Patreon backer</strong></a></p><p>The six-month quest for a new prime minister ended this week when former spy chief Dick Schoof accepted his own Mission Impossible: keeping the new right-wing cabinet afloat. Good news for his predecessor, Mark Rutte, who can now concentrate on collecting the last stamps he needs to become boss of Nato. We look ahead to next week’s European elections, which have been beset by allegations of Russian influence and Danish disenfranchisement. Women have become more independent in the last 50 years, but teenagers are still feeling the after-effects of the pandemic. And a Dutch Lego superfan is ordered to take his custom-made train sets apart or pay the price.</p><p><iframe frameborder="no" height="300" scrolling="no" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/1834281168&amp;color=%23ff5500&amp;auto_play=false&amp;hide_related=false&amp;show_comments=true&amp;show_user=true&amp;show_reposts=false&amp;show_teaser=true&amp;visual=true" width="100%"></iframe></p><div style="font-size: 10px; color: #cccccc; line-break: anywhere; word-break: normal; overflow: hidden; white-space: nowrap; text-overflow: ellipsis; font-family: Interstate,Lucida Grande,Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Sans,Garuda,Verdana,Tahoma,sans-serif; font-weight: 100;"><a href="https://soundcloud.com/dutchnewsnl" rel="noopener" style="color: #cccccc; text-decoration: none;" target="_blank" title="Dutch News">Dutch News</a> · <a href="https://soundcloud.com/dutchnewsnl/the-pulling-a-dick-out-of-a-hat-edition-week-22-2024" rel="noopener" style="color: #cccccc; text-decoration: none;" target="_blank" title="The Pulling A Dick Out Of A Hat Edition - Week 22 - 2024">The Pulling A Dick Out Of A Hat Edition – Week 22 – 2024</a></div><p><strong>Ophef of the week</strong>: <a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/nicki-minaj-apologises-to-fans-after-schiphol-drugs-arrest/">Drug-smuggling diva Nicki Minaj fights the law, law wins</a></p><p><strong>Coalition news</strong></p><p><a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/new-prime-minister-dick-schoof-will-represent-all-the-dutch/">New prime minister Dick Schoof pledges to represent “all the Dutch”</a></p><p><a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/dutch-pm-mark-rutte-remains-optimistic-about-nato-job/">Outgoing prime minister Mark Rutte remains optimistic about Nato job</a></p><p><strong>Other news</strong></p><p><a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/dutch-parties-are-not-big-on-eu-election-info-in-english/">Few Dutch parties publish EU election information in English</a></p><p><a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/more-eu-nationals-sign-up-to-vote-in-the-european-elections/">More EU nationals sign up to vote in European elections</a></p><p><a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/russian-propaganda-probe-linked-to-dutch-meps-assistant/">Forum voor Democratie office raided in Russian propaganda probe</a></p><p><a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/its-important-to-have-a-strong-lobby-for-dutch-interests/">BBB interview: “It’s important to have a strong lobby for Dutch interests”</a></p><p><a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/schiphol-cityhopper-death-was-suicide-airport-police-confirm/">Schiphol airport police confirm death in Cityhopper engine was suicide</a></p><p><a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/seven-in-10-dutch-women-are-now-financially-independent/">Seven in 10 Dutch women are now financially independent</a></p><p><a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/dutch-teenagers-feel-less-healthy-and-happy-and-more-stressed/">Dutch teenagers feel less healthy and happy and more stressed</a></p><p><a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/court-orders-dutch-lego-fan-to-stop-selling-custom-train-sets/">Court orders Dutch Lego fan to stop selling customised train sets</a></p><p><strong>Sport</strong></p><p><a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/koeman-drops-maatsen-timber-and-olij-from-final-euro-2024-squad/">Koeman drops Maatsen, Timber and Olij from final Euro 2024 squad</a></p><p><a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/amsterdam-police-chief-frank-paauw-chosen-as-new-knvb-chairman/">Amsterdam police chief Frank Paauw chosen as new KNVB chairman</a></p><p><a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/we-need-to-level-up-dutch-come-up-short-again-in-tri-series/">Dutch cricketers fall just short again in tri-series defeat to Ireland</a></p><p> </p><p> </p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-primary btn-sm" href="/life-in-the-netherlands/podcast/"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/uncategorized/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=236249</guid><pubDate>Fri, 31 May 2024 10:18:43 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Gordon Darroch]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Arjen Lubach calls it quits on VPRO and Avondshow</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/arjen-lubach-calls-it-quits-on-vpro-and-avondshow/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-236246 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-art-and-culture"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Arjen Lubach calls it quits on VPRO and Avondshow</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-05-31T08:55:17+00:00"> May 31, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-236254" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_236254"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="960" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/1280px-Arjen_Lubach_with_Josh_Meyers_at_Boom_Chicagos_25th_anniversary_at_Carre.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/1280px-Arjen_Lubach_with_Josh_Meyers_at_Boom_Chicagos_25th_anniversary_at_Carre.jpg 1280w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/1280px-Arjen_Lubach_with_Josh_Meyers_at_Boom_Chicagos_25th_anniversary_at_Carre-560x420.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/1280px-Arjen_Lubach_with_Josh_Meyers_at_Boom_Chicagos_25th_anniversary_at_Carre-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/1280px-Arjen_Lubach_with_Josh_Meyers_at_Boom_Chicagos_25th_anniversary_at_Carre-768x576.jpg 768w" width="1280"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-236254"> Arjen Lubach with Josh Meyers at Boom Chicago's 25th anniversary. Photo:  AwesomeACM</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Arjen Lubach is quitting broadcaster VPRO after the next season of the satirical news show De Avondshow.</p><p>“After three years, Arjen and his team will be doing one more season of the popular satiral news show. His plans for the future are as yet unknown,” the VPRO said.</p><p>Lubach, who shot to world fame with his Trump spoofing video “<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ELD2AwFN9Nc">America first, the Netherlands second”,</a> said he was thankful to the VPRO “for giving me the space to make satirical programmes,” he said.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>The broadcaster has traditionally been home to innovative programme makers, such as <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M6PmLTOuwWc">Van Kooten en de Bie</a> , <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=z1Abfmg3k7g">Wim T. Schippers</a>, and A<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iiyGVvA6KfU">rjan Ederveen and Tosca Niterink. </a></p><p>Lubach said he will not stop altogether but that it is time for “new adventures”’. “Making funny television shows is in my blood so the Netherlands is not rid of me yet,” he said.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/art-and-culture/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=236246</guid><pubDate>Fri, 31 May 2024 08:55:17 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Hanneke Sanou]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Pro-Putin party may have key role in senate for new Dutch gov’t</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/pro-putin-party-may-have-key-role-in-senate-for-new-dutch-govt/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-236250 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-election-2023 category-politics category-senate"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Pro-Putin party may have key role in senate for new Dutch gov’t</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-05-31T08:43:51+00:00"> May 31, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-60818" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_60818"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="400" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/senate.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/senate.jpg 600w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/senate-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/senate-560x373.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/senate-300x200.jpg 300w" width="600"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-60818"> The senate</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The new right-wing coalition will rely on the support of other far-right parties in the upper house of parliament to pass controversial legislation, and that means the pro-Putin Forum voor Democratie could have a key role.</p><p>Between them, the PVV, VVD and BBB have 30 of the 75 seats and need to find another eight senators to have a majority. The NSC is not represented in the upper house.</p><p>Forum voor Democratie, with two senators, JA21 with three and the fundamentalist Christian group SGP with two, would provide seven of the much-need eight, while 50Plus and regional party senators OPNL could make up the difference.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>TV current affairs show Nieuwsuur reported on Thursday evening that the far-right parties would be prepared to support the fledgling coalition, including FvD, which is characterised by its support for Russia and conspiracy theories.</p><p>The VVD’s senate leader Edith Schippers, for example, told the programme she had always “worked very well” with the two FvD senators, while BBB’s senate chief Ilona Lagas said she had always been treated with respect.</p><p>“We will look at this government constructively,” FvD senate chairman Johan Dessing said. “I think it important that we in the senate look at how we can make this country better”.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Nevertheless, Dessing said he had problems with former spy chief Dick Schoof as prime minister, saying “he is the one who brought back jihadi brides in 2016”. This was a reference to Schoof’s role in bringing Dutch women who had gone to Syria and Iraq to join IS back to the Netherlands.</p><p>Martin van Rooijen, the sole 50Plus senator, said he wished that the new government’s policy plans had included something about pensions. “There we could do business,” he said.</p><p>During Thursday’s lower house debate on early retirement, none of the 37 PVV or seven BBB parliamentarians were present.</p><h2>Senate’s role</h2><p>The senate’s main duties are in the legislative field, but it also plays a role in scrutinising the actions of the government.</p><p>Formally the senate can only reject or accept legislation but in practice, however, it has rather more options and can require ministers to make amendments to legislation or give commitments to how it is implemented.</p><p>Recently, for example, the senate rejected plans to increase the minimum wage after BBB senators voted against. The BBB is the biggest party in the upper house.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/election-2023/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/politics/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/senate/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=236250</guid><pubDate>Fri, 31 May 2024 08:43:51 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>“Larger than Life” Dutch football anthem features the players</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/larger-than-life-dutch-football-anthem-features-the-players/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-236236 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-art-and-culture category-euro-2024-sport category-sport"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> “Larger than Life” Dutch football anthem features the players</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-05-31T07:47:25+00:00"> May 31, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-236244" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_236244"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="990" sizes="(max-width: 1466px) 100vw, 1466px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Screenshot-2024-05-31-at-09.45.43.png" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Screenshot-2024-05-31-at-09.45.43.png 1466w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Screenshot-2024-05-31-at-09.45.43-560x378.png 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Screenshot-2024-05-31-at-09.45.43-1200x810.png 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Screenshot-2024-05-31-at-09.45.43-768x519.png 768w" width="1466"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-236244"> A still from the video, which has English subtitles</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Star DJ Armin van Buuren, indie pop band Chef’Special and the players themselves feature on the Dutch team’s anthem for this summer’s European Championships in Germany.</p><p>Van Buuren and Chef’Special wrote <em>Larger than Life</em> and roped in the team to provide backing vocals for the first time since André Hazes’ 1988 belter <em>Wij houden van Oranje</em>. The song is completely in English.</p><p>“The track combines the unity, the ambition and the passion needed to win the Championship in Germany this summer” the KNVB football association <a href="https://www.onsoranje.nl/node/81442">said</a>.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Parts of the track with the players were recorded during a writers’ camp held at the same time as the players’ training camp. In the <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=01STUt1wU_A&amp;t=3s">video</a> Virgil van Dijk can be seen leading the players in the vocals and claps accompanying the song.</p><p><iframe allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" frameborder="0" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/01STUt1wU_A?si=U7Qcnjtbg1jLxOWC" title="YouTube video player" width="560"></iframe></p><p>“I really enjoyed working with the team,” Armin van Buuren said on a mini documentary about the making of the song. “Our track embodies the faith in making the dream come true. That cup is ours!” he said.</p><p>Oranje, in Group D together with Poland, France, and Austria, kick off their campaign against Poland on June 16 in Hamburg.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/art-and-culture/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/sport/euro-2024-sport/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/sport/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=236236</guid><pubDate>Fri, 31 May 2024 07:47:25 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Hanneke Sanou]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Inflation stable at 2.7% in May, preliminary figures show</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/inflation-stable-at-2-7-in-may-preliminary-figures-show/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-236237 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-economy category-inflation"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Inflation stable at 2.7% in May, preliminary figures show</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-05-31T07:29:02+00:00"> May 31, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-236238" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_236238"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="900" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/inflatie.jpeg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/inflatie.jpeg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/inflatie-560x420.jpeg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/inflatie-768x576.jpeg 768w" width="1200"/></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Inflation remained stable at 2.7% in May, according to preliminary estimates from national statistics office CBS.</p><p>Energy, including motor fuels, food and drink, and services all cost more, but the price of industrial goods fell, the CBS said.</p><p>Calculated according to EU methodology, which excludes the impact of rental housing, inflation was also 2.7% in May, up marginally from 2.6% in April.</p><p>Eurozone inflation was 2.4% in April, according to the most recent figures from European statistics agency Eurostat.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/economy/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/inflation/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=236237</guid><pubDate>Fri, 31 May 2024 07:29:02 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>More Dutch youngsters are claiming welfare benefits</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/more-dutch-youngsters-are-claiming-welfare-benefits/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-236234 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-benefits category-jobs"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> More Dutch youngsters are claiming welfare benefits</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-05-31T07:22:37+00:00"> May 31, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-221300" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_221300"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="768" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/3BE5B18D-9C11-45D4-BE42-CF44787ACB4A_1_105_c.jpeg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/3BE5B18D-9C11-45D4-BE42-CF44787ACB4A_1_105_c.jpeg 1024w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/3BE5B18D-9C11-45D4-BE42-CF44787ACB4A_1_105_c-560x420.jpeg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/3BE5B18D-9C11-45D4-BE42-CF44787ACB4A_1_105_c-768x576.jpeg 768w" width="1024"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-221300"> Photo: Dutch News</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The number of young adults claiming basic welfare benefits rose 8% over the year to end-March, reaching 39,000, national statistics agency CBS said on Friday.</p><p>It was the fifth quarter in a row that more youngsters up to the age of 27 had been claiming the benefit.</p><p>CBS chief economist Peter Hein van Mulligen said that young adults are more likely to claim welfare (bijstand) than unemployment benefit (ww) if they lose their jobs because they have not built up enough time in work to qualify.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>The increase in claims is much higher than among other age groups, and there was no increase at all in claims by the over-45s.</p><p>Last quarter, 403,000 people in the Netherlands were claiming welfare benefit, despite the tightness on the jobs market. That is a rise of 1% on a year ago.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/benefits/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/jobs/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=236234</guid><pubDate>Fri, 31 May 2024 07:22:37 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Police arrest six airport workers for drug smuggling</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/police-arrest-six-airport-workers-for-drug-smuggling/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-236227 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-cocaine category-crime category-schiphol-2 category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Police arrest six airport workers for drug smuggling</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-05-31T07:05:04+00:00"> May 31, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-186755" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_186755"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="667" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Depositphotos_521971748_S.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Depositphotos_521971748_S.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Depositphotos_521971748_S-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Depositphotos_521971748_S-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Depositphotos_521971748_S-768x512.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Depositphotos_521971748_S-640x427.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Depositphotos_521971748_S-92x62.jpg 92w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Depositphotos_521971748_S-130x87.jpg 130w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-186755"> Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Dutch military police have arrested six men for drug smuggling at Schiphol airport.</p><p>The men, who were arrested over several months, all worked at companies operating from Schiphol, allowing them easy access to the airport, the Marechaussee said on<a href="https://x.com/Marechaussee/status/1796422921239384350?ref_src=twsrc%5Egoogle%7Ctwcamp%5Eserp%7Ctwgr%5Etweet"> social media.  </a></p><p>An anonymous tip about cocaine hidden in pallets coming from Suriname prompted an investigation by police, customs and the tax office criminal investigation unit FIOD.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>“We found that we were dealing with an “airport broker”, a person who approached people who work at the airport to smuggle drugs. (..)  They were well-organised and their passes allowed them to be at the airport. You need people in different areas to be able to get the drugs past security,” a police spokesman told broadcaster NOS.</p><p>A former airport worker, a 48-year-old man from Diemen, liaised between the broker and the other workers. The men had positions in logistics, transport and package delivery at the airport.</p><p>During raids of the men’s homes in Almere Amsterdam and Diemen, police confiscated documents, expensive cars, and €124,000 in cash and cryptocurrencies.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Police said criminal activity at the airport is difficult to eradicate. “People are people. If they are prepared to look away when things like this happen for a wad of cash, we must do all we can to prevent it from happening,” he said.</p><p>The six men, aged between 32 and 51, will be tried as members of a criminal organisation, the public prosecutor said. “These people all had a security pass. Sometimes one or two people are arrested who have passes but in this case, there were six and that is a serious matter,” the spokesman said.</p><p>Some 60,000 people work at Schiphol who have all been screened.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/cocaine/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/crime/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/schiphol-2/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=236227</guid><pubDate>Fri, 31 May 2024 07:05:04 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Hanneke Sanou]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Vlaardingen foster child, beaten into hospital, called for help</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/vlaardingen-foster-child-beaten-into-hospital-called-for-help/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-236226 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-abuse category-children category-crime category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Vlaardingen foster child, beaten into hospital, called for help</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-05-31T07:02:17+00:00"> May 31, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-227530" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_227530"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1333" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L.jpg 2000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L-560x373.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L-1200x800.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L-768x512.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L-1536x1024.jpg 1536w" width="2000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-227530"> Photo: Depositphotos</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The foster parents of a 10-year-old girl who is fighting for her life in hospital have been remanded in custody while the police investigation continues.</p><p>Judges ordered the couple, known as Daisy and John van den B, to remain in jail for a further 14 days while police and social workers try to find out what went wrong. Another foster child and the couple’s own biological child have been removed from the family home in Vlaardingen, near Rotterdam.</p><p>Meanwhile, more details about the girl’s efforts to get help have been emerging, raising serious questions about the role of social workers and the lack of checks on foster parents.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Sources have told the <a href="https://www.telegraaf.nl/nieuws/737852262/nieuwe-gruwelijke-details-over-pleegmeisje-10-vlaardingen-urenlang-vastgebonden-leek-op-marteling">Telegraaf</a> that the girl has been so physically abused that it “resembles torture” and that she was often tied up for hours at a time. Her head had also been shaved, ostensibly because she had lice. She was also spotted in the garden last summer, weeding with a broken arm.</p><p>The girl, who was placed with the family in March 2022, is now known to have made efforts to get help at a local supermarket and at school several months ago, saying she had been beaten. Several people, including neighbours, have also reported the situation to the authorities.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Sources told the paper questions were also raised about the suitability of the couple to raise foster children last summer when it turned out they were advertising themselves as swingers on sex websites, and offering to meet others at their home.</p><p>The girl’s biological mother told the paper via a spokesman that she is only allowed to visit her daughter in hospital with the say so of the William Schrikker Groep, the  private foundation in charge of the girl’s welfare.</p><p>The foundation has refused to comment on its role in the scandal, saying only that it has reported the situation to government inspectors.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/abuse/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/children/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/crime/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=236226</guid><pubDate>Fri, 31 May 2024 07:02:17 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Schiphol Cityhopper death was suicide, airport police confirm</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/schiphol-cityhopper-death-was-suicide-airport-police-confirm/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-236223 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-accidents category-amsterdam category-schiphol category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Schiphol Cityhopper death was suicide, airport police confirm</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-05-31T06:35:15+00:00"> May 31, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-235672" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_235672"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1536" sizes="(max-width: 2048px) 100vw, 2048px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2048px-PH-EXI_KLM_Cityhopper_Embraer_ERJ-175STD_ERJ-170-200_at_Schiphol_AMS_-_EHAM_The_Netherlands_pic6.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2048px-PH-EXI_KLM_Cityhopper_Embraer_ERJ-175STD_ERJ-170-200_at_Schiphol_AMS_-_EHAM_The_Netherlands_pic6.jpg 2048w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2048px-PH-EXI_KLM_Cityhopper_Embraer_ERJ-175STD_ERJ-170-200_at_Schiphol_AMS_-_EHAM_The_Netherlands_pic6-560x420.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2048px-PH-EXI_KLM_Cityhopper_Embraer_ERJ-175STD_ERJ-170-200_at_Schiphol_AMS_-_EHAM_The_Netherlands_pic6-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2048px-PH-EXI_KLM_Cityhopper_Embraer_ERJ-175STD_ERJ-170-200_at_Schiphol_AMS_-_EHAM_The_Netherlands_pic6-768x576.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2048px-PH-EXI_KLM_Cityhopper_Embraer_ERJ-175STD_ERJ-170-200_at_Schiphol_AMS_-_EHAM_The_Netherlands_pic6-1536x1152.jpg 1536w" width="2048"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-235672"> Photo: Alf van Beem/ Wikimedia Commons</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The man who died at Schiphol airport after becoming caught up in the motor of a KLM Cityhopper had deliberately climbed into the engine, Dutch border police said on Thursday evening.</span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The aircraft had just completed the pushback procedure and was about to taxi to the runway when the man climbed onto the </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">aircraft</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">.  He worked for a Schiphol operating company. </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">“The investigation has revealed that he intentionally climbed into the engine, indicating this is a case of suicide,” the police said in a short statement. “Out of respect for the victim and their loved ones, </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">no further statements will be made</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">.”</span></p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The AD said the incident had a “major impact” on the crew and passengers who had seen it happen. </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">KLM Cityhopper flies with small aircraft from Brazilian manufacturer Embraer </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">which</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> can take between 88 and 132 passengers.</span></p><p><em><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Anyone struggling with suicidal thoughts can chat with someone anonymously at </span><a class="editor-rtfLink" href="http://www.113" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><span data-preserver-spaces="true">www.113 or</span></a><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> ring the free number 0800-0113.</span></em></p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/accidents/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/amsterdam/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/amsterdam/schiphol/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=236223</guid><pubDate>Fri, 31 May 2024 06:35:15 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item></channel></rss>